Back Course registration

Your course plan shows all the courses you are registered for and have planned for the future. From this overview you can navigate to other self-services, such as the study guide and Canvas.

You can plan courses in the current academic year if the registration term has not started yet by clicking ‘plan course’. The same applies to courses in future academic years. Once the registration term has started, you will receive a notification that you can register for courses. You register for planned courses via ‘register course’.

In the registration screen please select all activities such as lectures, seminars and exams. After you have finished a course your result will be displayed.

By selecting the (planned) course a window will be displayed with more details. You can print your study plan by clicking the PDF icon.

Proposed courses
All courses
Minor / specialization
Via ‘All Courses’ you can search within the courses on offer at the VU. Courses matching your search term and the selected period are listed on top, and courses in other periods are listed below. Only courses within your programme of study, the extracurricular course offering and available minors are displayed. To participate in courses of other programmes you need permission.
Clicking on the name of a course displays more information about it and allows you to add it to your planned courses or – if registration is open – register for it. In the top right-hand corner you can opt for these modules to be displayed as a list rather than a table.
More information on course registration can be found on VUnet.

View courses in all periods

Search for courses within your programme of study, extracurricular courses on offer and within minors. Click on a course for more details and to register. Click to see what possibilities are available if you cannot find a course.

Bachelor third year
After the registration deadline has passed you can no longer register for courses. The option of last-minute registration is offered for a limited amount of courses. This means that you can register for available places in selected courses from Tuesday 0.00 until Wednesday 23.59 in the week prior to the start of a course. More information can be found here.

Bachelor third year
After the registration deadline has passed you can no longer register for courses. The option of last-minute registration is offered for a limited amount of courses. This means that you can register for available places in selected courses from Tuesday 0.00 until Wednesday 23.59 in the week prior to the start of a course. More information can be found here.
